One pound of body weight is roughly equivalent to 3500 calories, so eating an extra 500 calories per day will cause you to gain one pound a week.
Crossing your arms behind your back, and stretch your shoulders and chest while seated helps yout posture.
Eat breakfast every day. People who eat breakfast are less likely to overeat later in the day. Breakfast also gives you energy and helps you think and learn.
Use fats and oils sparingly. Olive, canola, and peanut oils, avocados, nuts and nut butters,olives, and fish provide heart-healthy fat as well as vitamins and minerals.
Eat six meals a day instead of heavy three meals.
Drink 10 glasses of water everyday. Its especially important to stay well hydrated when following a comprehensive training, nutrition, and supplementation program.
Don’t take more than one all-purpose multivitamin daily.
Never cut any food group out of your diet including carbohydrates.
Take a deep belly breath for three to five minutes twice a day.
Have a greater variety of food. Variety means no excess of anything and more nutrients. Eat three different foods at every meal.
Learn to cook and gain control of what goes into your meals
Eat calcium-rich foods like milk, cheese and green leafy vegetables.
Don’t sit for a prolonged time. Stand up and stretch.
Honey helps build up your immunity system.
